<section id="Adding_a_New_Catalog_Item" remap="TID_44350">
	<title>Adding a New Catalog Item</title>
	<para>
		Use this procedure to add a new service catalog item using the dashboard UI.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Services</guimenu><guisubmenu>Catalog</guisubmenu></menuchoice> and select <guimenu>Catalog Items</guimenu> in the accordion menu.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Configuration</guibutton>, then click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1848.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Add a New Catalog Item</guibutton>. The <guilabel>Adding a new Service Catalog Item</guilabel> window is displayed.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/7146.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
			<para>
				Choose <literal>Orchestration</literal> from <guilabel>Catalog Item Type</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				In <guilabel>Basic Info</guilabel>, add <literal>Name</literal> and <literal>Description</literal>. Select the <guiicon>Display in Catalog</guiicon> box.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/7147.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
			<para>
				Select the <literal>Catalog</literal>, <literal>Dialog</literal>, and <literal>Orchestration Template</literal> from their respective list.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Select Provisioning Entry Point. The default is <literal>/Cloud/Orchestration/Provisioning/StateMachines/Provision/default</literal>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Add</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>